<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,209,264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Legs uniformly brown. Hind femur distinctly thickened, about three times longer than wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,273,321,345]" box="[146,273,321,345]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis box="[146,273,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" box="[146,786,361,385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Body length 
<quantity box="[295,377,361,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
(male), wing length 
<quantity box="[616,698,361,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
(male).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[269,415,394,418]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2Aâ€“B</figureCitation>
) brown, triangular in profile, about 1.4 times longer than high; frons not strongly produced beyond anterior level of eye, in profile about 0.25 times as long as long axis of eye; gena prominently broadened posterad, anteriorly strongly narrowed below eye; parafacial about 0.05 times as long as long axis of eye. Frontal triangle trapezoid, occupying most area of frons, reaching its anterior margin and semicircular anteriorly; ocellar triangle and surrounding area black; area between eye and frontal triangle depressed and brown-yellow. Setulae and setae on head dark brown. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[472,586,617,641]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
) brown; pedicel blackish 0.7 times as long as third antennal segment; third antennal segment nearly rectangular, 1.3 times longer than wide, rounded apically, with black dorsal margin; arista pale yellow with brown basal segment, pale short pubescent. Proboscis and palpus pale yellow with pale setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Thorax black, slightly narrower than head; anterior portion of humerus brown, propleuron and upper portion of anepimeron yellow; mesonotum 1.1 times longer than wide, with prominent setigerous punctures; scutellum two times wider than long, with yellow margin. Setulae and setae on thorax pale; katepisternum with some long thin setulae. Legs brown; hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[630,746,904,928]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
) short and distinctly thickened, about three times longer than wide and 2.4 times thicker than fore femur; hind tibia somewhat curved. Setulae on legs pale; hind femur with some long setulae. Wing hyaline; veins mostly brown. Relative lengths of costal sections second:third:- fourth54.5:5.8:4. Squama yellow with pale setulae. Halter blackish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Abdomen blackish, light microtrichose; dorsum rugose lightly; venter brown. Setulae and setae black, venter with some pale setulae. Genitalia (
<emphasis box="[901,919,1097,1120]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">â€ž</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation box="[944,1090,1096,1120]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2Eâ€“F</figureCitation>
): epandrium dark brown, longer than wide, with some long setae; surstylus dark brown with many short setulae, its apex narrow, short and directed inward; cercus black with some setulae; hypandrium pale, in dorsal view higher than wide; gonites separated by a distinct suture; pregonites convergent and rounded apically; both distal ends of postgonites acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,280,1336,1360]" box="[146,280,1336,1360]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis box="[146,280,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,385,1377,1401]" box="[146,385,1377,1401]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<collectingCountry box="[146,215,1377,1401]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[232,373,1377,1401]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,267,1457,1481]" box="[146,267,1457,1481]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis box="[146,267,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,1497,1553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
The Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[342,396,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">brevi</emphasis>
- means short and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[724,802,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">femura</emphasis>
means femur. The epithet of the species refers to the short and distinctly thickened hind femur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,245,1610,1634]" box="[146,245,1610,1634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis box="[146,245,1610,1634]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[146,1103,1650,1706]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cherian" authorityName="Cherian" authorityYear="1978" box="[551,889,1650,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganta">
<emphasis box="[551,787,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Platycephala giganta</emphasis>
Cherian
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1025,1650,1674]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">India</collectingCountry>
in the lateral shape of head and distinctly thickened hind femur, but can be easily separated
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[213,1169,168,225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="405">
from the latter by the entirely brown hind femur. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cherian" authorityYear="1978" box="[834,951,169,193]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganta">
<emphasis box="[834,951,169,193]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="405">P. giganta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hind femur is yellow, but partly brown-black (
<bibRefCitation author="Cherian PT" box="[586,745,201,225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="405" pagination="137 - 141" refId="ref4112" refString="Cherian PT. 1978. The genus Platycephala (Diptera: Chloropidae) from India. Orient Insect. 12 (1): 137 - 141." type="journal article" year="1978">Cherian 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
